		<div id="comment_body_65306739"><p>&gt; 93 million CT examinations were carried out in 2023</p><p>So the average person gets a CT scan every three years? Over 20 in their lifetime? That is crazy - the risk of a CT scan is pretty well understood, so why do we use it like candy?</p><p>European countries do far fewer CT scans, with better health outcomes, although the numbers are rising, too.</p></div>
